<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F02FF95FC36FC9CFBAFFCD5" authorityName="Risso" authorityYear="1810" box="[983,1103,794,820]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Gobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="auratus">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F02FF95FC36FC9CFC0BFCD5" box="[983,1003,794,820]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F02FF95FC18FC9DFBAFFCD5" box="[1017,1103,795,820]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">auratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
morph 2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F02FF95FF26FCB8FB48FC9C" blockId="55.[151,1437,290,1036]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
Habitat. Infralittoral species, known from 
<quantity id="2E379B383F02FF95FD7DFCB8FD10FCB9" box="[668,752,830,856]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.65" metricValueMax="3.2" metricValueMin="0.1" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" unit="m" value="16.5" valueMax="32.0" valueMin="1.0">1–32 m</quantity>
depth on mixed sandy-rocky habitats, rock crevices or stones nearby soft bottom, sometimes covered with seagrass (Herler &amp; Patzner 2005; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F02FF95FBEAFCE4FB7CFC9C" author="Louisy, P." box="[1035,1180,866,893]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refId="ref60639" refString="Louisy, P. (2015) Europe and Mediterranean Marine Fish Identification Guide. 3 rd Edition. Eugen Ulmer Ed., Paris, 512 pp." type="book" year="2015">Louisy 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F02FF95FF26FC00FAAEFBED" blockId="55.[151,1437,290,1036]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
Geographic distribution. Mediterranean. Recorded from many places from the Balearic Islands to 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F02FF95FB16FC00FAA7FC41" box="[1271,1351,902,928]" name="Turkey" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F02FF95FAB2FC00FEF4FC25" author="Fricke, R. &amp; Musa Sari, H." pageId="55" pageNumber="56" pagination="1 - 169" refId="ref54778" refString="Fricke, R., Bilecenog ˘ lu, M. &amp; Musa Sari, H. (2007) Annotated checklist of fish and lamprey species (Gnathostomata and Petromyzontomorphi) of Turkey, including a Red List of threatened and declining species. Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde, Serie A (Biologie), 706, 1 - 169." type="journal article" year="2007">
Fricke 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F02FF95FF76FC2DFF29FC25" box="[151,201,938,964]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">et al</emphasis>
. 2007
</bibRefCitation>
), including 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F02FF95FE78FC2CFE0BFC25" box="[409,491,938,964]" name="Croatia" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Croatia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F02FF95FE1AFC2CFCF6FC25" author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Patzner, R. A." box="[507,790,938,964]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" pagination="177 - 206" refId="ref58470" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Patzner, R. A. (2011) North-Eastern Atlantic and Mediterranean Gobies. In: Patzner, R. A., Van Tassell, J. L., Kovacic, M. &amp; Kapoor, B. G. (Eds.), The Biology of Gobies. Science Publishers, Jersey, British Isles, pp. 177 - 206. https: // doi. org / 10.1201 / b 11397" type="book chapter" year="2011">Kovačić &amp; Patzner 2011</bibRefCitation>
), Crete (Kovačić 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F02FF95FC3DFC2DFBEEFC25" box="[988,1038,938,964]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">et al</emphasis>
. 2011), 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F02FF95FB8DFC2CFB5DFC25" box="[1132,1213,938,964]" name="Cyprus" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Cyprus</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F02FF95FB2DFC2CFF3DFC09" author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Golani, D." pageId="55" pageNumber="56" pagination="89 - 91" refId="ref58212" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Golani, D. (2007 a) First record of three gobiid species in the Levant. Cybium, 31 (1), 89 - 91. https: // doi. org / 10.26028 / cybium / 2007 - 311 - 013" type="journal article" year="2007">Kovačić &amp; Golani 2007a</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F02FF95FEFDFC48FEBDFC09" box="[284,349,974,1000]" name="Libya" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Libya</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F02FF95FE8DFC48FD4BFC09" author="Al-Hassan, L. A. J. &amp; El-Silini, O." box="[364,683,974,1000]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" pagination="291 - 301" refId="ref50837" refString="Al-Hassan, L. A. J. &amp; El-Silini, O. A (1999) Check-list of bony fishes collected from the Mediterranean coast of Benghazi, Libya. Revista de Biologia Marina y Oceanografia, 34, 291 - 301." type="journal article" year="1999">Al-Hassan &amp; El-Silini 1999</bibRefCitation>
). Also recorded in Gran Canaria, Atlantic (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F02FF95FB6CFC48FA84FC08" author="Dooley, J. K. &amp; Van Tassell, J. V. &amp; Brito A." box="[1165,1380,974,1001]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" pagination="1 - 49" refId="ref53046" refString="Dooley, J. K., Van Tassell, J. V. &amp; Brito A. (1985) An annotated check-list of the fishes of the Canary Islands. American Museum Novitates, 2824, 1 - 49." type="journal article" year="1985">
Dooley 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F02FF95FB08FC49FAFAFC09" box="[1257,1306,974,1000]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">et al</emphasis>
. 1985
</bibRefCitation>
), but this needs to be confirmed because of taxonomic progress on the 
<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F02FF95FC92FC74FBC1FBED" authorityName="Risso" authorityYear="1810" box="[883,1057,1010,1036]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Gobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="auratus">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F02FF95FC92FC74FBC1FBED" box="[883,1057,1010,1036]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Gobius auratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex since this record.
</paragraph>
